
[1]legalize

   LE'GALIZE, v.t.

   1. To make lawful; to render conformable to law; to authorize. What can
   legalize revenge?

   2. To sanction; to give the authority of law to that which is done
   without law or authority. Irregular proceedings may be legalized by a
   subsequent act of the legislature.
